# Drag-Adjust Numeric Input (Mandatory Default)

**Status:** Program-wide policy (2026-06). All block-editor and dialog numeric fields use drag-adjust spin boxes instead of stock `QSpinBox` / `QDoubleSpinBox` with up/down arrows.

## Required widgets

| Type | Widget | Use for |
|------|--------|---------|
| Integer | `DragAdjustSpinBox` | ms delays, coordinates, repeat counts, poll intervals |
| Decimal | `DragAdjustDoubleSpinBox` | thresholds, fractional values |

Both live in `src/ui/widgets/`. **Do not** add raw `QSpinBox` / `QDoubleSpinBox` in UI code unless the user explicitly requests stock spinners.

## Behavior

1. `setButtonSymbols(QAbstractSpinBox::NoButtons)` — no stepper arrows.
2. `Qt::SizeHorCursor` on the field.
3. **Single click** (no drag past threshold) enters text input on the line edit; **horizontal drag** anywhere on the field adjusts the value.
4. Line edit installs an `eventFilter` on the spin box so drags work over the text area too; use `QApplication::startDragDistance()` before drag starts.
5. Modifier multipliers per drag step (every 4 horizontal px by default), based on `singleStep()`:
 - Default: `singleStep()` (int) or `singleStep()` (double)
 - Shift: ×10
 - Ctrl: ×100
5. Keyboard typing and wheel still work via base class; suffix labels (e.g. `ms`, `회`) stay on separate labels where used (`WaitEditor::makeMsInputRow`).

## Anti-patterns

- Stock `QSpinBox` / `QDoubleSpinBox` in editors or feature dialogs
- Re-enabling up/down buttons on drag-adjust widgets
- Custom one-off drag logic instead of extending the shared widgets

## Key files

- `src/ui/widgets/DragAdjustSpinBox.*`
- `src/ui/widgets/DragAdjustDoubleSpinBox.*`
- Reference editors: `WaitEditor`, `ImageFindEditor`, `ClickEditor`, `FeatureEditDialog`

Full policy: [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) — **§8.7 Drag-adjust numeric input**.
